<paragraph blockId="7.[831,1437,1428,2000]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[831,946,1428,1451]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">Remarks:</emphasis>
Moricand did not state on how many specimens his description was based. In his second paper he placed this taxon in the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName authority="Wagner" authorityName="Wagner" authorityYear="1827" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicidae" genus="Helix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pyramidella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">Helix pyramidella</emphasis>
Wagner
</taxonomicName>
in Spix, 1827 (
<bibRefCitation author="Moricand S." pageId="7" pageNumber="64" pagination="415 - 446" refId="ref31033" refString="Moricand S. 1836. Memoire sur les coquilles terrestres et fluviatiles, envoyees de Bahia par M. J. Blanchet. Memoires de la Societe de physique et d'histoire naturelle de Geneve 7 (2): 415 - 446." type="journal article" year="1836">Moricand, 1836: 418</bibRefCitation>
), and ‒ on the next page ‒ as one of the several varieties (evidently colour forms) of this species. There he mentioned “Ayant reçu, depuis la publication de mon premier Mémoire (…), un grand nombre de variétés de cette coquille, j’ai reconnu que mon 
<emphasis box="[1255,1436,1686,1709]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">H. Blanchetiana</emphasis>
rentre dans l’espèce de Spix, dont elle n’est qu’une des variétés que je classe ainsi”. The current lot has 
<specimenCount box="[831,982,1783,1806]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" type="generic">63 specimens</specimenCount>
altogether, which are thus a mixture of the original lot and shells received later and (partly) considered as varietal forms by 
<bibRefCitation author="Moricand S." box="[1188,1433,1848,1871]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" pagination="415 - 446" refId="ref31033" refString="Moricand S. 1836. Memoire sur les coquilles terrestres et fluviatiles, envoyees de Bahia par M. J. Blanchet. Memoires de la Societe de physique et d'histoire naturelle de Geneve 7 (2): 415 - 446." type="journal article" year="1836">Moricand (1836: 419)</bibRefCitation>
. It is impossible to untangle this lot completely. One shell, which best approaches the original figure of Moricand, is figured herein. The current systematic position follows 
<bibRefCitation author="Simone L. R. L." box="[1011,1227,1977,2000]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" refId="ref32400" refString="Simone L. R. L. 2006. Land and freshwater molluscs of Brazil. EGB / Fapesp, Sao Paulo, 390 pp." type="book" year="2006">Simone (2006: 148)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
